Summary

Confirmed the vulnerable streaming surface was still present in HEAD, then added deny-by-default local file access controls for NLP MCP streaming reads: configured sandbox roots, canonical path containment checks, regular-file enforcement, and max file-size rejection before reading/streaming content.

Hardened URL-backed dataset loaders so remote reads require an explicit BEEP_NLP_MCP_ALLOWED_URL_HOSTS hostname allowlist and enforce BEEP_NLP_MCP_MAX_REMOTE_BYTES while reading response chunks, before a full response body is materialized.

Documented the new streaming access-control environment variables and default-deny behavior in the package README.

Updated integration-test fixtures to opt into their temporary sandbox roots and added regression coverage for out-of-sandbox local file reads and non-allowlisted URL loads.

Committed changes on the current branch: b48f31cd fix(nlp-mcp): sandbox streaming file and url reads.

