+### Streaming tool access controls
+The streaming toolkit accepts caller-supplied paths and URLs, so the stdio server
+uses deny-by-default access controls:
+- `BEEP_NLP_MCP_ALLOWED_ROOTS` — comma-separated directories that local file tools
+ may read. When unset, only `./nlp-mcp-data` below the process working directory is
+ allowed. Symlinks are canonicalized and must remain within an allowed root.
+- `BEEP_NLP_MCP_MAX_FILE_BYTES` — maximum regular-file size accepted by local
+ streaming tools (default: `10485760`, 10 MiB). Directories, devices, FIFOs, and
+ other non-regular files are rejected.
+- `BEEP_NLP_MCP_ALLOWED_URL_HOSTS` — comma-separated URL hostnames that dataset
+ loading tools may fetch. When unset, URL reads are rejected. Loopback, link-local,
+ and private/internal hostnames remain blocked even if listed.
+- `BEEP_NLP_MCP_MAX_REMOTE_BYTES` — maximum response body size returned by URL
+ loaders (default: `10485760`, 10 MiB).

